        "section_id": "really-started",
        "label": "The Origin",
        "label_color": "#b45309",
        "heading": "Where It Really Started: \n3AM, Wide Awake, \nAsking “Why?”",
        "paragraph_1": "It was 3AM in a small hostel in Reykjavik. My backpack was stuffed with \"just in case\" shirts, yet I had nothing clean to wear for the glacier hike the next morning. The smell of travel—stale, lived-in, exhausted—filled the small room.",
        "paragraph_2": "I realized then: Odor is a wall. It stops you from moving freely. It forces you to carry burdens you don't need. I spent the rest of that night staring at the ceiling, wondering why, in a world of self-driving cars and pocket supercomputers, our shirts still failed us after one day.",
        "highlight_text": "",
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/photo-1520250497591-112f2f40a3f4.avif",
        "image_alt": "",
        "caption": "Iceland, 2017"
      }
