                "text_Dzgk9y": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:blocks.text.name",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>I didn't go to fashion school. I taught myself textile engineering out of necessity. I spent years experimenting with copper ions, volcanic ash, and plant-based polymers, reading papers on microbiology and fiber physics late into the night.</p><p>Fashion designers care about how a shirt looks on a runway. I care about how it smells after a 14-hour flight. My obsession isn't style—it's the human experience.</p>",
